title: Beatrice
creator: Henry Rider Haggard
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of Beatrice, by Henry Rider Haggard. Read by Michele Eaton. Beatrice is a lonely twenty-two year old woman. After saving Geoffrey's life, they fall in love. However, Geoffrey is married. In addition, a local rich land owner wants to marry the beautiful Beatrice. This is a romance by the author of King Solomon's Mines, Allen Quatermain, and She." (Summary by Stav Nisser) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B 01-20 (174MB) Download M4B 11-31 (99MB)
